category.name: Any% (No AJS)
category.rules:
**Timing: **

• Runs use the Real Time Attack (RTA) timing convention, which means it measures the real time that has passed from start to finish, rather than in-game time. Runs may be timed with an external timer (such as WSplit), though the timer DOES NOT have to be shown on video.

• Timing starts when the first cutscene (Francis Intl. Airport) is skipped and ends when control is lost when the cutscene where the firetruck with Tenpenny falls off the bridge in End of the Line starts.

**Runs require video evidence. The video must show:**

• The [initial load of the game.](http://i.imgur.com/fgwlv6Z.png)

• The entire duration of the run from start to finish (breaks for stream drops are excusable if minor) without edits or cuts.

**Additionally:**

• [Arbitrary Jump in Script](https://www.reddit.com/r/speedrun/comments/ddrsfd/grand_theft_auto_san_andreas_skip_that_saves_over/) isn't allowed.

• Any saved replays (such as ones viewed by pressing F3) used must be recorded during the run.

• Any save files loaded must be made during the run.

• The [Frame Limiter needs to be set to ON](http://i.imgur.com/oa8pk15.png) in the advanced graphics options for the duration. 

• All modifications besides the ones [listed here](https://www.speedrun.com/gtasa/thread/ar4sg) are banned.

• Cheats (including accidental) are banned.
